      "content": {
        "title": "High-Risk Stress Fracture Locations",
        "definition": "Anatomic sites where nonunion risk mandates aggressive treatment including femoral neck tension side, anterior tibia, navicular, and proximal fifth metatarsal.",
        "summary": "High-risk fractures often require operative stabilization and prolonged protected weight-bearing."
      },
